      "id": 345845,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Divalent carbon species called <i>carbenes</i> are capable of fleeting existence. For example, methylene, :CH<sub>2</sub>, is the simplest carbene. The two unshared electrons in methylene can be either paired in a single orbital or unpaired in different orbitals. Predict the type of hybridization you expect carbon to adopt in singlet (spin-paired) methylene and triplet (spin-unpaired) methylene. Draw a picture of each, and identify the valence orbitals on carbon.</p>\n",
